{
  "texts": [
    "For Falcon-RW-1B and TinyLLaMA-1.1B, DRaFT-Q achieves 3-6The core insight of DRaFT-Q-that adapter capacity should evolve dynamically during training-opens up promising directions for future fine-tuning strategies.",
    "Rather than statically assigning architectural parameters, DRaFT-Q adapts rank allocation using exponential moving averages of layer-wise curvature, enabling localized growth where learning is most active.",
    "Combined with reward-guided token prioritization, this makes DRaFT-Q a step toward more biologically-inspired and context-sensitive optimization in neural networks.Future extensions of DRaFT-Q include:• Scaling to larger models.",
    "DRaFT-Q has shown stability on LLaMA-2-13B and can be applied to 70B+ models with appropriate infrastructure (A100s, H100s, or model parallelism).",
    "The method is model-agnostic and does not require architecture changes."
  ]
}